ladies a plate
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:request for women to bring a plate of food, to a party etc.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:plate (bring a plate)
Pronunciation:
Notes: [AND 1961: OED(S b 18h.] to provide food as (part of) an admission fee to a function.
